  "idea": "Remove the video editor loading screen ('Opening video editor / Loading your latest timeline...') in src/tools/video-editor/pages/VideoEditorPage.tsx. Three changes: (1) In VideoEditorPage's auto-select effect (around lines 210-248), prefer settings.lastTimelineId from useToolSettings over timelines.data[0], so when the user has previously opened a timeline in this project we seed the ?timeline=... URL param immediately without waiting for the useTimelinesList network round-trip. (2) Prefetch tool settings / the timelines list when navigating to the video editor \u2014 find the navigation link/button to /video-editor (likely in a sidebar or nav component) and either prefetch the data or append ?timeline=<lastTimelineId> directly so the URL already has the timeline ID on first paint. (3) Replace the current Card placeholder (lines 274-288 in VideoEditorPage.tsx, the 'Opening video editor' card) with return null so there's no visual flash during the brief gap. Do NOT do a full refactor to hoist the editor chrome out of VideoEditorProvider \u2014 that's out of scope. Keep the error card path (timelines.error) intact. Follow CLAUDE.md project conventions.",
